column5: Someone's gotta start it...if you can get to it yet, how much water is there? Curious if you can blow through there or not. Also if houseboats will be able to go through or if it is the haul to Devils Elbow
So true! "Someone has to start it" is hilarious.
With the high water levels, there is nothing to talk about.

acually lac suel is the opposite super low in the spring and rises as the summer goes on.talked to a guy yesterday that has a camp not far from deception landing.said the water is about six feet away from the cribbing on his dock.don't know about the rags though.
He must have been pulling your leg. The water level is very high for this time of year. check out the web site.http://www.lwcb.ca/pdf/LacSeulGraph2014.05.21.pdf

Agreed. Lac Seul is very high for this time of year. Water isn't usually this high on Lac Seul until late June. i'll be blowing through the rags in a boat full speed ahead. Can't comment about houseboats though, I have no idea how much water they need.
Just to hijack my own thread, Hey Ben or anyone else for that matter, I would venture a guess that the Chute (Abrams/Minnitaki) will have plenty of water as well?
Chutes are a non-issue, could drive right up the middle right now.
a few too many beers i guess.

Over the years I have passed through the rags in a 65' houseboat as early as the first week of June. GPS elevation including the antenna offset was at 1169 feet (actual water level). This is the lowest reading I have ever had going through there. Watch out for the stump at the north end. I know that stump fairly well.
